text: Marion County is a county in the U.S. state of Iowa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 33,414. The county seat is Knoxville. It was founded in 1845 and named for Francis Marion, a brigadier general from South Carolina in the American Revolutionary War. == References == == Other websites == * Official Marion County, Iowa Website Category:1840s establishments in Iowa Territory Category:1845 establishments in the United States Category:Iowa counties
title: Marion County, Iowa
